T. W. Mulqueen, Owner of THE Boat EMMA T. GRIMES, Libelant-Appellee, v. THE Steamtug WILLIAM TRACY, Tracy Towing Line, Inc., Claimant-Appellant; THE Steamlighter INDUSTRY, New York & New Jersey Steamboat Company, Claimant-Appellee. No. 213. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. Feb. 17, 1930. Macklin, Brown, Lenahan & Speer, of New York City (Horace L. Cheyney, of New York City, of counsel), for appellant. William P. Purdy, of New York City (John E. Purdy, of New York City, of counsel), for libelant-appellee. Alexander, Ash & Jones, of New York City, for appellee-claimant.

Before MANTON, SWAN, and AUGUSTUS N. HAND, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Decree affirmed, with costs.
